https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/blob/main/x-pack/plugin/transform/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/xpack/transform/checkpoint/DefaultCheckpointProvider.java#L116

When `remoteClusterResolver.resolve(transformConfig.getSource().getIndex())` returns no results, the `ActionListener<Map<String, long[]>> listener` is never called, causing the Transform to be started but stuck in `indexing`.

Any subsequent call to the `stats` API will cause the API call to timeout and the transport task to hang indefinitely.

